Those methods at least used to exist (I work on a fork). Those two functions on the DecoratedSignature can be used to do something like this to see who has signed a transaction envelope:
```js
  const signers = account.signers
  const transactionSignatures = transaction.signatures.map((sig: any) => sig.signature())

  return signers.filter(kp => transactionSignatures.some(sig => kp.verify(transaction.hash(), sig)))
```

I just reviewed the source code files again and still didn't find those.

```
struct DecoratedSignature
{
  SignatureHint hint;  // last 4 bytes of the public key, used as a hint
  Signature signature; // actual signature
};
```

